{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#2417: Compiler optimization with css module",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:28:11.271719+00:00",
  "text": "Compiler optimization with css module\n\n### What problem does this feature solve?\r\nRef: https://twitter.com/Linus_Borg/status/1310844386536718339?s=20\r\n\r\nVue 3 compiler currently cannot treat CSS module classes as static.\r\nWe might have some way of dealing with it.\r\ne.g. mark it as static or pre-compile the css module class as a static string.\r\n\r\nPOC: https://github.com/yoyo930021/vue-pre-css-module/blob/main/src/index.ts#L67\r\nIn this POC, I try to use `NodeTransform` for pre-compile the css module class as a static string.\r\nBut it lacks information on several key operations.\r\nMainly related to the path and settings.\r\n\r\nI think there are two ways to achieve this.\r\nOne for more information on NodeTransform.\r\nOne is built into `vue-loader` or `@vue/compiler-dom`.\r\n\r\n### What does the proposed API look like?\r\nNo\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: compiler",
    "scope: sfc"
  ],
